Description: Sherd of East Greek pottery open vessel, bowl or possibly a lid; inside glazed; outside part of possible guilloche band and a frieze containing uncertain motif; incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 21.2.10)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.72)
